<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7716&amp;p=33634#p33634"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Andy.Smalley wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Before I start downloading utilities and running test on this problem, can someone please confirm.denne that if I completely uninstall Classic Shell with a PRO uninstaller, including all registry entries being removed, and then reinstalling the same version I have been using V3.6.8. will it reset all my setting back to how it was originally? or am i now at a state where something on the Windows setting is offsetting the Classic shell program.<br />what I have now found is that the start menu button has a overlay button, and this is why my menus keep changing, strange because I have not added any custom buttons? but sometimes I get the classic button with the flag on the left and the text START on the right, other times I am getting the ORB graphic with the START text?<br />It is all strange, and still it bleeds through full screen videos.<br />Someone please help.<br /></div>The normal uninstallation for Classic Shell keeps user settings but removes all program files. This is intentional so if the user needs to reinstall or update, all settings are preserved. To remove all Classic Shell Settings, use the Utility: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.mediafire.com/download/3ukeryzw41qpfz8/ClassicShellUtility.exe">http://www.mediafire.com/download/3uker ... tility.exe</a><!-- m --><br /><br />There is no need to use any third party uninstaller as the Utility will do the best job of completely and cleanly removing Classic Shell.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Sat Aug 12, 2017 3:16 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
