Can  anyone help me out  please?<br />I  have been running Classic shell on my PC for the last 3 years with no issues,<br />I love the program and have installed it on every PC I have configured since finding out how fantastic it works.<br />But recently I had an issue with my Comodo internet security that forced me to have to a remote desktop with one of their gurus.<br />The guru, completely reset all the views if my Windows 7 Home premium.<br />He managed to hide all the  Classic tools icons that appear in all the windows, I have now got these back but the icons are larger then they were, that is my first issue.<br />The second issue is, whenever I play a video online the start button pops through the video when in full screen.<br />My third issue is, when I press the windows start button with left mouse button, I get the vista start menu with 2 rows, this is not what is selected, but if I physically press the windows start button, I get the correct XP style single start menu.<br />Also I have noticed that the start button sometimes changes is appearance? I have an old version from 3 years ago and the start button is a plain START, with no graphics, but sometimes it comes up with a start button with graphics.<br />It is all very strange.<br />What I want to know is can anyone help me sort out all these issues individually, or should I just uninstall it and reinstall, my problem is if I reinstall will it remember my prefs/settings and just return back to how it is now rather then returning to how it was?<br />Alos I could use &quot;my uninstaller pro&quot; that will remove all traces of installation, including all registry edits.<br />Sorry for the long winded post but I would love to get this all sorted as it is really messing with my brain.<br />Thanks in advance<br />Andy<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21349">Andy.Smalley</a> — Mon Jul 03, 2017 1:06 am</p><hr />
